summary_comment: Elizabeth is an excellent yoga instructor known for her expertise and friendly demeanor. Students consistently praise her for creating a relaxed and enjoyable class atmosphere, and many appreciate that she often allows them to leave early.

Ratings.comment: Elizabeth is a really nice lady, and she knows yoga well.. She almost always lets you out early too.
I'd take this class again and again. Great teacher and great class to add in your schedule.
Ms Miller is a fabulous teacher! Relaxed class atmosphere. Fun and learned alot.
great teacher. makes yoga fun and understandable

summary_comment: Coach Sherri is highly regarded for her caring and accepting approach, making her classes engaging and supportive. Professor Louis is praised for her caring nature, engaging workouts, and high standards, encouraging students to put in effort for better results. Both instructors are noted for their accessibility and ability to make courses enjoyable and stress-relieving, with flexible retake options.

Ratings.comment: Coach Sherri is amazing, she's incredibly caring and is very accepting of anything comes up. she uses videos that are very engaging and overall very supportive, definitely plan on taking this course again!!

Professor Louis was very caring about all her students, It's a very engaging workout class, the more effort you put in the more you get out of it. she won't let you get anything other than a perfect on the quizzes, very understanding if you can't make a class, i recommend everyone to take her class!!

Mrs. Sherri is an amazing instructor who genuinely cares about her students. She was accessible outside of class and made the class fun and wanted the students to view the course as a way to "de-stress." Great course for 1 credit hour, you can take this course up to 3 times I believe. Aside from that, my quads grew around 1 1/2 inches

summary_comment: The professor is highly knowledgeable and passionate about the subject matter, which makes for an engaging yet sometimes lengthy lecture. While some find the sessions can be monotonous, the grading is straightforward, and the material is well-covered in lecture slides. The professor sets high expectations for professionalism and participation, though students generally find these classes worthwhile and recommend them.

Ratings.comment: I have really enjoyed his class this semester, even at 8am. His lectures can be long sometimes, but he is always respectful about getting out of class on time or early. You can tell he truly cares about what he is teaching. Grades are pretty straight forward in exams, quizzes, and attendance. Be ready to participate in class from time to time.

Very knowledgeable about the topic, but lectures can get drony. Exams were pretty easy and all the answers could be found in the lecture slides. Very professional, unlike other professors but justified in his reasoning.

Good professor who is clearly very knowledgable and passionate about the content he teaches. However, he expects a level of professionalism that I haven't experienced in other classes. Not a bad thing, just a different teaching style. All in all, worth the slight extra effort to be slightly to take one of his classes. Highly recommend.

summary_comment: This professor is highly regarded for his exceptional teaching quality and engaging classroom atmosphere. Students appreciate his dedication to ensuring effective learning and his approachable, personable demeanor. His classes, while covering technical material through quizzes, are considered enjoyable and rewarding, with many recommending his courses.

Ratings.comment: What an amazing guy! He really cares about how well students are learning, and makes class so fun! There's a few quizzes for the class, they are a little technical, but not too difficult. I've had him 3 times and he's been amazing every time! Very personable

Gordon is super cool and easy going, and perfect for teaching strength classes! I wish I could have taken his class in person to get to know him more and be able to get feedback right away, but the online class was still fun and I learned a lot from him. I would recommend Gordon!

As long as you put forth your best effort in his tumbling classes, youll get a good grade. Its only 1 credit hour so take his classes because you want to learn. He gives great feedback and is willing to work with you to help you get past anything youre having trouble with. Great guy!
He Cool

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for her approachability and effective teaching methods, making the course accessible and engaging. Students find the material relevant and the class structure straightforward, though they note that discussions require effort. Overall, the course offers valuable insights into health and fitness and can be completed with minimal stress, leading to an easy A with consistent effort.

Ratings.comment: Health class with 5 modules over the semester. Everything's available at the beginning of the semester and easily doable within the time frame. The project at the end of the class is the only big problem, but start on it early and you won't have any problems. Easy A with unlimited time on the exams.

She is a great professor. I took this course online, and it is an easy A if you're willing to put in the minimal work. All the content is interesting, and you will learn a lot of health/fitness-related things.

Super caring, nice & good listener. If u want to improve ur wellbeing take this class bc it involves a lot of self-reflection & personal evaluation. Have to buy a book-thing to access the course. 4 modules w multiple chapter readings (completion), activities, a discussion, & a final reflection. Must put in effort for discussion posts. Easy A
Great professor -- approachable, cooperative, caring.

Alex is very approachable, and the content taught in Strength Training is extremely applicable to real life. She will help correct your form and will aide in developing your personal fitness plan. Great professor for a really fun class.

Shes a great teacher, and this is a great class. If you want to learn more about strength training, working out, or general fitness, this class is perfect. The class is set up like a gym session, where she goes over the workouts at the beginning of class. There are some short quizzes outside of class, but overall its fairly straightforward.

summary_comment: Valerie is an excellent instructor who effectively teaches beginners, ensuring that all students fully understand the exercises through her thorough approach.

Ratings.comment: I loved this class! Valerie is a great instructor. This course is great for beginners, and she takes the time to make sure everyone understands all of the exercises completely.

summary_comment: Professor Torrie is highly regarded for her caring and relaxed teaching style, with minimal homework focusing on reflections and attendance at weekly yoga classes. Students consistently praise her genuine interest in their well-being and her ability to create a calming and beneficial learning environment through her yoga instruction.

Ratings.comment: she was great!! there were only 2 small assignments and everything else was just showing up to class. she genuinely cares about all her students and I highly reccommend her!!

Professor Torrie is an incredible yoga instructor and I would take class from her any day. She's super understanding with any complications and all she really wanted was for you to put in the effort and to get something out of this class. She is so wise and gave incredible advise for mindfulness. Two "essays" and two 30-second skills assessments.

The weekly yoga lab was the 2nd part of the stress management course. All you really had to do was show up to class. Her yoga was always so relaxing and different from the normal yoga classes I've taken. 10/10 recommend.

Best class and best professor ever!! She gives very few assignments that are mostly reflections based on class activities or textbook exercises (meditation and relaxation techniques). She provides personalized feedback on every assignment and shows that she truly cares about each of her students! You just have to attend the yoga class once a week.

Yoga I is an easy A and Torrie is the best professor for this class. Only two writing assignments (very easy, completed in less than 10 minutes). Attendance is mandatory because it is only one credit hour. However, after a little while, an hour and 50 minutes of yoga got a little boring. If you like yoga and want an easy A, take this class.

TAKE THIS CLASS. It was so nice to have an easy A and relaxing class. It is the perfect break from hard classes. Her voice itself is calming and makes meditation so easy. She is so nice and calm. She really wants you to relax, succeed and enjoy yoga. Learning yoga is so beneficial to your body and mind.

Ruth is truly such a sweetheart. I enjoyed her yoga class so much and hope to take another one soon! She has a very calming voice which helps when you are doing yoga and meditating. She loves what she does and always is willing to help. I appreciate her so much.
This class was a perfect way to de-stress and Ruth knows so much about yoga so it was a very interesting class!

This class was great. She takes suggestions at the end of the semester to improve the class and really cares what people think. We have weekly assignments that are easy, but she takes time to read and sometimes respond to them and she really does care what we're thinking in our responses. Super sweet lady and great yoga instructor as well.

summary_comment: The professor is described as a nice individual but is criticized for making the 1-credit-hour class feel overly serious and strict, which detracted from potential enjoyment. Overall, his teaching quality is acknowledged, though with room for a more engaging approach given the class format.

Ratings.comment: His class could've been more fun, he was a nice professor but for a 1-credit-hour class, it felt too serious and strict

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for her dedication and kindness, though her classes are described as very time-consuming and focused on busy work rather than substantive learning. While some students found value in the content and appreciated her teaching style, others struggled with the workload and found the material pseudo-scientific or repetitive. Overall, her yoga courses emphasize attendance and personal reflection but can be challenging and demanding.

Ratings.comment: OK for STEP Crystal-worshipper who explained that piezoelectric vibrations from crystals (a real phenomenon) has effects on your health (pseudo-scientific nonsense). Took group to OSU astronomical observatory and asked an astronomer to discuss how the alignment of the planets has effects on your health via changes in cosmic electromagnetic waves.

DO NOT TAKE YOGA 1 FOR AN EASY A!!! This class is very time consuming and the quizzes every Friday are impossible. This course was hybrid and she would post hours of video lectures every week. Deb is such a nice lady but, she is the type of person that thinks her class is the most important thing in your life.
Really enjoyed Yoga1. Learned lots of things about yoga and holistic wellness in general.

Class is split into 2 portions: lecture & yoga. Meet 2x a week: once for each portion. Grade based on attendance, weekly reflection papers, weekly quizzes on textbook readings, and one final paper. Mainly just busy work but she's an easy grader. Lectures are very boring. I suggest getting an online textbook for the quizzes so you can "cntrl-f" it

I took her yoga 1 course and was encouraged to take Stress Management thinking it was easy. This class is annoying with busy work. She will not give grades or feedback until the last few weeks so if you did anything wrong you will be penalized multiple times for the same thing and lectures seem redundant. I only look forward to sleeping in the lab.

had never taken a yoga course before and i really enjoyed her class and how she taught it. wanted you to be more leveled with your body than do any crazy poses. if you skip more than 2 classes you drop 3 letter grades. nice change of pace from regular classes.

Fantastic instructor! Had never done yoga before but wanted to try it, and definitely wasn't disappointed. Learned so many useful things about alignment, balance, etc. Keep an open mind (you may not agree with everything) and you'll get lots of helpful insight that you've probably never heard before. Such a nice lady with a knack for instructing :)

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for her engaging and accessible teaching style, with a focus on discussion and practical application of material. Students appreciate her clear communication, friendliness, and motivation, though some note that exams require thorough preparation. Overall, the class is seen as a valuable and enjoyable way to boost GPA and improve understanding of health-related topics.

Ratings.comment:
Loved her! 3 modules covered before an exam. 3 total exams and an optional final. Class is discussion based and there's not
mandatory attendance. 2 credit hours and a good GPA booster.

Completely online class, but laid out expectations very clearly, was accessible, and seemed very kind. Helped promote a cardio event I worked on, which was not something she had to do. Great GPA boost and helps you keep in shape.

Very nice professor. Understands that its not a main priority class. Encourages class discussion. Asks questions throughout lectures and has every person go around to share their thoughts in front of class. She shares basic information that is important to know. The assignments were all online and took maybe an hour max each week. Easy A class.

Class seems easy but exams are super specific and most of the material is not discussed in class. Peters herself is wonderful. She’s super friendly and the class itself is kind of fun. Beware that this isn’t the easy A it may seem to be. Weekly assignments are easy, exams are not.

Jennifer is so nice and I loved taking her course! this class was easy. you had 3 modules and in each module you have 3 chapters to read, a few quizzes/surveys, and then one concluding quiz that was easy. you have a few papers to write but they are super short (like 1 page double spaced) and she grades based on effort :). also offers extra credit !

Her assignments arent just about getting to know or understand the material but applying the information to your personal life. I absolutely love the integration of this material. The written portions are graded on genuine effort on your part and the guided assignments were incredibly helpful in remembering the material. 10/10 recommend this class
Intro to Health is a fascinating class, and is pretty self-explanatory. You can complete assignments early, and prof is accessible if needed.

Not a lot of assignments because it is not about your intelligence, but your fitness. She is amazing at motivating people, even at 8 am. She is very kind, energetic, and understanding, but you do have to go to class. Super Easy A and I would definitely take any of her classes again. Helps students understand how to workout.

She definitely knows her stuff. You'll definitely learn a lot. However, for an exercise class I think she assigns too many papers. We actually had to a presentation in class which I didn't do in my last exercise class.

Jennifer is good at what she does. Grade wise, you may need to do is take an hour to prepare for the mid-term performance test.  The final exam is a piece of cake.  Mine was online and open-note.  Jennifer is also very nice and learns everyone's names, and gives them feedback for improvement.  It's a chill class, but you need to show up.

I had her for Intro to Health which was an extremely easy class.  She is passionate about what she teaches, so she makes the lectures interesting.  There is a textbook for the class to do the online assignments, but you don't have to read it to do the homework.  It's required for some majors, but even if it's not required, I definitely recommend.

I had her for kickboxing and is a really nice professor. She is very clear with her grading criteria and policies and abides by them. The kickboxing class is more like a cardio class with kickboxing elements so if you are looking for something that pertains more to fighting, you'll have to look elsewhere. Try the boxing course.
I had her for racquetball. She is such a nice and helpful teacher and she makes an appoint to help you have fun and enjoy the class, even if you're not good at the activity
She may seem kind of crazy at first, but shes really nice. Pilates can be hard at times, but shes very good at getting you to understand what shes trying to say.

summary_comment: The professor's class is perceived as monotonous and difficult to endure, with strict adherence to rules and repetitive weekly activities that make it feel long and unengaging. However, she is viewed as caring and respectful, effectively teaching essential first aid and CPR skills, thereby enhancing students' confidence in their abilities.

Ratings.comment: The class was easy but painfully boring. She's strict about phones, and Mondays felt like the slowest two hours of my life—endless lectures and group work. Wednesdays were an hour of stretching, making me feel both antsy and sleepy. It was the same thing every week; impossible to sit through. She means well, but makes this class a struggle.
She is a caring and respectful professor. Did a good job teaching me the basics of first aid and CPR and I feel much more confident in my abilities.

SEI.Subject: KNSFHP
SEI.Class Name: Stress Management for the College Student

summary_comment: Kyle is an effective and knowledgeable golf professor who maintains a relaxed teaching environment. He excels at assessing and improving students' swings and is particularly adept at explaining golf rules and strategies to help reduce handicaps.

Ratings.comment: Kyle is a very chill and relaxed golf professor and knows what he is talking about. Can help assess your swing and help change it for the better. Kyle is very helpful with teaching the rules of golf and helping you lower your handicap.

summary_comment: Bud is an exceptional instructor who effectively prepares students for skydiving through comprehensive and repeated reviews of critical protocols. However, one student had a negative experience with a scam related to his services, warning others not to engage with him financially.

Ratings.comment: Scammer $400 non-refundable and denied service. DONT TAKE

Bud is an amazing instructor! Skydiving seemed so terrifying but after taking his course I felt so prepared. You learn a lot of information within a few classes, so make sure to study the important protocols he stresses in class. He includes all of the information on his slides and reviews multiple times. I would recommend his class to anyone!

summary_comment: This professor is highly regarded for her exceptional teaching quality, demonstrated by her understanding and flexibility, especially accommodating out-of-state students with conflicting schedules. Students find her approachable, fun, and supportive, with many expressing a strong desire to retake her class.

Ratings.comment: I literally love this woman she is such a good teacher and she is so understanding. I'm an out of state student so whenever I'd go home I'd have flights that would conflict with class time and she was totally understanding and is overall easy going. She's fun and helpful, I'd 100% take this class again.

SEI.Subject: KNSFHP
SEI.Class Name: Stress Management for the College Student

summary_comment: Seamus is widely regarded as an exceptional and entertaining professor, known for creating a fun and engaging classroom environment. Students appreciate his enthusiasm, care for both the subject matter and his students, and his ability to make each class enjoyable and brighten their week. His teaching style emphasizes a relaxed atmosphere where participation and enjoyment are prioritized over rigorous grading.

Ratings.comment: This will be the easiest class you take. He is hilarious and class is fun but also not mandatory. Class is graded on three assignments and you basically get an A for writing your name. Highly recommend for a fun two credit hours.

Seamus is literally the best teacher ever. I love his icebreaker questions that he does every class to get his students involved and chatting. This class is just show up, play ping pong, and have a good attitude. Seamus is a great teacher too but knows fun is the most important part. I want to take another one of his classes but they're filled :(

Will not find yourself a more enjoyable class or professor. Cares about his material and cares about his students even more. If you can find 2 hours a week to show up to his lectures I highly recommend taking to just brighten up your week.
Super enthusiastic and kind. Just show up.

Sha is the best! He always makes my day so much better and I look forward to his class every week. Once a week isn't enough!I am one of the only girls in the class, but Sha always makes sure my opinions stay valid. LOVE him and I am planning on taking more courses with him since he brightens up my day! :)
AMAZING! I would take any of his classes. He has been my favorite professor by far!
I took this class as a fun elective and it definitely was enjoyable! It had a very laid back atmosphere and was something I looked forward to going to. Would love to take another class with Sha!
Greatest professor I've had at OSU. Genuinely cares about his class and brings passion every week. I'm a senior but I wish I had taken every class that he offers.

This was truly one of my absolute favorite classes I've ever taken and Sha is one of the best professors here. He creates a fun class environment and something to look forward to each week. One day a week of Seamus Reilly simply is not enough. I hope other people can be as lucky as me and get to enjoy having the opportunity to learn from him.
Absolute GOAT. If you can take a class with Sha do it. He is layed back, you just get credit to talk and you don't really need to show up. He is really funny and loves to teach.

Seamus is a really great professor. Couldnt have asked for a better coach for soccer. Still in the class at the moment and enjoy every moment of it. He really works hard to engage his students, encourages teamwork, and makes sure youre having fun. Highly recommend taking a class with him if you have the chance!

I loved table tennis with Sha! He made the environment so much fun and told some pretty funny stories. He gives an automatic A+ to everyone, even if you don't show up but why take the class if you don't want to show up? The only thing I would say is I wished there was less talking and more playing. And it took a while to set up the tables...
Seamus is hilarious. His class was basically a discussion with only three brief assignments all semester. His class was the easiest I've ever taken.

There were 4 assignments about sports the whole semester and pretty much if you turn them in and they are a page long you get the credit. There were zooms but they were not mandatory. Never went to a class just did the assignments and got an A.

Seamus is the absolute best. I took his soccer class and he is super friendly. The classes are really fun and I learned a lot while also being allowed to just enjoy playing soccer. If you are new to soccer, you have to take this course!
The GOAT
If you don't skip class, you'll get an A. Table tennis was really fun, probably my favorite class. He is always in a good mood and is great to be around. Includes everyone. Highly recommend.

Sha genuinely cares about being the best you can be. He can be a bit over the top but its all in good fun. Take a class with him. "It will change your life" - Sha. He lives by that, and in all honesty it will.
He's the man what can I say. Really good at soccer and teaching.
Sha is the bomb. Man is a rare combo of hilarious, competitive, humble, and insightful. Took table tennis and would take any of his classes.

Took a soccer class with Sha and he was absolutely amazing! Very passionate about soccer and loved getting to coach us while we learned a couple skills he wanted us to work on. Lots of play time and very fun class.

summary_comment: Sara is highly regarded for her effective teaching methods, making complex topics accessible and engaging through her lighthearted approach and sense of humor. Her courses are praised for their straightforward nature, requiring minimal additional study beyond reading the provided free online textbook. Students consistently recommend her courses for their balance of learning important skills and achieving good grades with relative ease.

Ratings.comment: First aid/cpr with Sara was great, she is nice and funny so it keeps the course lighthearted. Modules are easy and to study for exam you just read the textbook (which is a nice read not too wordy and free given to you online). 7 weeks, easy A, and you learn important skills 10/10 recommend!

summary_comment: Julie is highly regarded for her dedication and care in teaching self-defense and boxing, making students feel comfortable and ensuring they gain valuable knowledge. Her classes, while occasionally challenging with some material being hard to recall, are generally praised for their supportive and accessible nature. Despite the hybrid format due to COVID, she managed to maintain a positive learning environment.

Ratings.comment: Julie was such an amazing teacher who truly cared for her girls in self-defense. I highly recommend this class to anyone who would like to learn self-defense, as Julie is open to discussion no matter what the topic is and helps her students feel comfortable.

I really liked this class. I could tell that she cared about her students and wanted them to take as much away from the course as possible. Assignments are vlogs and article quizzes which are extremely easy. The final was okay as it was hard to remember things said in the beginning of the course and there's nothing to refer back to.

I am not athletic at all, so I was kind of nervous going into boxing, but Julie did a wonderful job at explaining things so that I felt more at ease. Because this class was hybrid bc of covid, it wasn't as fun as it could of been, but she did a great job despite that. I'd def recommend anyone take this class to learn a little about boxing.

summary_comment: Dan is an excellent teacher known for making his beginner wall climbing class both informative and enjoyable. He effectively communicates essential skills and fosters a positive learning environment. Students highly recommend his class for those seeking a fun Physical Education experience.

Ratings.comment: Dan is a great teacher and a fun person to be around. I took the beginner wall climbing class with him and he made it clear what we needed to know and how to do well climbing. I would definitely recommend his class if you're looking for a fun PE class.

summary_comment: Professor Kim is highly regarded for her exceptional teaching quality, characterized by her understanding, knowledge, and genuine care for her students. She creates a fun and inclusive learning environment and provides generous extensions and insightful feedback. Students strongly recommend her for any class they teach.

Ratings.comment: I took Kim for Wall Climbing and absolutely LOVED it. She is so understanding, knowledgable, and cares so much about her students. Highly recommend.

Kim was an amazing professor. She was understanding and made the class fun. Grade is dependent on attendance. Three main papers to write, including midterm. She was generous on extensions and made the course work easily understandable. Her feedback was very good and insightful. I would recommend her for any class.

SEI.Subject: SOCWORK
SEI.Class Name: Clinical Social Work with Children and Adolescents

summary_comment: Dr. Li is a knowledgeable professor who genuinely cares about his students' success and encourages them to work hard and maintain professionalism. However, his teaching style often leaves students feeling frustrated and confused, as the material is difficult to grasp during lectures. Despite this, some students appreciate his willingness to help and allow multiple attempts on assignments, finding the course content straightforward enough to pass with minimal attendance.

Ratings.comment: Every time I left Dr. Li's class, I felt so frustrated because we would literally use 90% of our class interpreting (not due to his accent, he was okay to understand that way) but the material he was trying to teach. It was absurd. He cares & has the knowledge, but couldn't teach it. We all left confused and knowing less.

He's hard to understand at times, I found it best to actually look at him when he's talking. He jokes around a lot and the class is really easy going. The material is pretty straightforward so even if you don't pay attention in class, you can pass easily. You're only allowed to miss 3 classes and that's really the only drawback.

Dr Li is my favorite professor I've ever had at OSU. He is always willing to help and just wants you to work hard and be "professional." In 521 he allowed us to re-do our assignments many times to get full credit. Even though there is a cultural barrier he is actually pretty funny when you can understand him.

SEI.Subject: KNPE
SEI.Class Name: Research on Teaching in Physical Education

summary_comment: Dr. Ward is highly regarded for his impactful teaching, known for provoking deep thought and fostering a supportive environment where students feel heard and valued. His dedication to personal connections and intellectual engagement is evident in his ability to transform students' perspectives significantly. While some initially found him challenging or reserved, most students come to appreciate his commitment and the substantial learning experience he provides.

Ratings.comment: Dr. Ward is hands down the best professor I have ever had. He thought provokes, talks about the hard things & listens intently. He learns every persons name, truly asks about your wellbeing. Every time I walked out of his class, I knew more about myself and was reminded why I went into sports coaching. He's the type that changes your life. AMAZING

At first I didn't like him, but my perception changed quickly. He is slightly arrogant, but he stands up for his students and as long as you are serious about your work he is easy to get along with and a good guy. Pretty easy class just buy tons of ink and printer paper for the 47 lesson plans you have to print out

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for their effective teaching methods and supportive approach. Students find the material accessible when paired with consistent attendance and preparation, and they particularly appreciate the instructor's assistance for those new to horseback riding. The classroom environment is noted for its safety and the calm demeanor of the horses used in lessons.

Ratings.comment: Allison and Rachel are great! Read your textbook and you can do all homework ahead of time. Be sure to show up for class every time and you will learn a lot. They are so helpful, especially with those of us that have never been around horses or ridden horses before. The horses are calm and safe.

summary_comment: Dr. Lower is highly regarded for her exceptional teaching skills, making complex topics accessible and engaging. Students appreciate her dedication to ensuring understanding and her supportive approach to learning. Her classes, whether in law or exercise, are praised for their enjoyable and effective format, focusing on active participation and practical application.

Ratings.comment: "Sport Law" seemed intimidating to me at first, however Dr. Lower made content easy to understand. She is such a great teacher and makes sure everyone understands what's going on. Grade was based on group participation, weekly online quizzes (multiple attempts), and a final project (easy/enjoyable). One of my favorite professors ever!

Prof. Lower-Hoppe is so sweet! She cares so much and wants everyone to succeed. Weekly quizzes, show up to class for participation points, and she really tries to make lectures interesting. The semester long project is a legal debate that's kind of tedious depending on your group mates. But class is pretty easy. You can tell she loves teaching!

One of my favorite professors that I had at Ohio State. She is so nice and really cares about her students. The class i was in was a Sport Law class and the main focus is to prepare us for the Mock Trial at the end of the semester. Overall I loved the class and she really makes sure you understand the material. 10/10

Ms. Lower is a very nice and understanding teacher.  She's very realistic and understanding.  I have an 8am class and she keeps me awake, which is saying a lot.  She's also not hard to look at!  Very pretty!  I highly recommend her.

She taught a cardio equipment class this quarter and I thought it was great.  She kept it interesting and really piqued my interest about exercising and staying in shape.  Awesome motivator, as she will do most of the exercises with the students, even the hard stuff. Definitely recommend.

SEI.Subject: KNPE
SEI.Class Name: Teaching Health and Fitness Courses at the College Level

summary_comment: This professor is highly regarded for his exceptional teaching quality and genuine care for his students, making him a standout educator. Students consistently recommend him without reservation.

Ratings.comment: Overall great human being, cares about his class and students. Highly recommend him.
This guy absolutely rocks

summary_comment: Professor Ryan's teaching quality is mixed; her weekly assignments are simple and quizzes are fair if students keep up with readings. However, she is unresponsive to emails, often delays grading assignments, and uses outdated presentations that offer little support. Overall, she is not recommended due to her lack of engagement and poor communication.

Ratings.comment: Pros: The weekly assignments are simple and the quizzes are fair as long as you take notes of the readings and look over them before the timed quiz. Cons: She doesn't always respond to emails and sometimes the assignments are not posted on time. The emails that she has sent out, which are very few, were unprofessional.

Professor Ryan is uninterested in helping students. Not only does she take more than three days (sometimes longer) to respond to emails, she takes well over a month to grade assignments. Her online class presentations are clearly outdated and it seems like all she does is uploads old presentations and offers no assistance. Would not recommend.

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for his teaching quality, offering an easy A for students who attend all classes. Known for his humor and willingness to answer questions, he creates a welcoming learning environment. Students strongly recommend taking his class.

Ratings.comment: There is no class attendance but many of the tests are taken in class. It is an easy A if you show up to all the classes. Feel free to ask questions He is a great prof and is very funny. I highly recommend you take this class with him.

summary_comment: Marty is an enjoyable instructor who makes the class easy and fun, though some students find the initial sessions challenging due to his high expectations. While he excels at creating a relaxed atmosphere, others feel the class can be unnecessarily difficult and lack patience. Overall, the class is recommended for those seeking a laid-back approach to swimming and diving.

Ratings.comment: Easy class and fun way to get exercise during the week. Marty is not the best guy and he's a little too caught up in swimming and times but overall it's an enjoyable class. Overall I would recommend the class.

He makes the class needlessly hard. He doesn't give you much time to get comfortable. Be prepared to spend most your time underwater looking for goggles. He isn't the most understanding. Classroom portion easy. Lifelong subs diver and expects you to be too
Marty is awesome and a laid back guy. Swim 2 is really easy and he is a blast to have.

summary_comment: The professor is widely regarded as either an excellent instructor who provides valuable insights and encouragement, or as arrogant and selective in his feedback. Students appreciate his approachability and care for their progress, though some find his teaching style and focus on tactical skills to be a deviation from traditional karate.

Ratings.comment: Arrogant and does not teach true karate but a mix of karate and tactical skills, would have been nice to know prior to taking the class. Very choosey on whom he wants to correct and whom he doesn't say anything towards. 0/10
Very good teacher, shares good insights to his students, very approachable and  listens well. I will take his classes again for sure.
Great teacher
he's a really good instructor and cares about our progress and makes sure that we do things right. he encourages us too and he's funny.
His boxing for beginners class was awesome. Great exercise and surprisingly informative. You'll learn how to throw a punch and a little about the sport itself in the process. Highly recommended.

summary_comment: This professor receives a perfect 10/10 rating for outstanding teaching quality, demonstrating exceptional clarity, engagement, and effectiveness in conveying complex material. Students consistently praise his ability to make the subject matter accessible and interesting.

This professor is highly regarded for her understanding approach and willingness to address students' questions, ensuring clear communication and support. She demonstrates a strong knowledge base, particularly in practical areas like strength training, and creates an engaging and fun learning environment. Students appreciate her encouragement and inclusive teaching style, making her classes both informative and enjoyable.

Ratings.comment: Great class. She's really understanding and willing to answer any questions. Good grader. Doesn't use Carmen much tho.

Took her Strength Training class. She was a very lenient professor and very knowledgeable. She always demonstrated new exercises for us before expecting us to do them. She also made the class fun. She would occasionally get side tracked and have fun discussions with the class. The class was very informative and helped me get into lifting a lot more
Lauren was amazing. She's down to earth and super encouraging to everyone in the class no matter what shape or size you are. LOVED her circuit training class and definitely would take it again!

summary_comment: Dr. Lehwald offers an easy class for those who attend lectures and follow instructions, with both the midterm and final exams being online. However, his grading can be strict, requiring precise adherence to rubrics. While some find his constant feedback and humor beneficial, others are frustrated by his disorganization, condescension, and nagging.

Ratings.comment: As long as you attend lectures and listen, the class is a breeze. Both the midterm and final are online. The only frustrating thing is Dr. Lehwald's grading -- make sure you follow rubrics word for word or he will take off points. Otherwise an easy and simple class

Although his constant nagging and excessive feedback is highly annoying, he really is helpful in making you become a better teacher. Seems very disorganized at times though. Can often be condescending and treat you like you're one of his high school students rather than an adult. Interesting sense of humor but overall a really good guy

summary_comment: This professor is easy to follow and very friendly, known for explaining concepts clearly. While not challenging, her classes remain engaging and prevent boredom. Students highly recommend her for any EDUPAES courses she teaches.

Ratings.comment: Easy
Really friendly, explains things well. Not the hardest class no matter who teaches it, but she keeps it from being boring. I would recommend her for any EDUPAES course she instructs.

summary_comment: Professor Wray's teaching approach focuses heavily on group projects and self-directed learning, which some students find ineffective for actual knowledge acquisition. While his classes avoid traditional testing, they rely on quizzes that can be challenging. Despite this, the grading is relatively easy, making it an "Easy A," though many find the learning process itself to be quite difficult.

Ratings.comment: I've taken two classes with Professor Wray, and i haven't learned anything in either one. His classes consist of group projects and group activities in class where you break up and teach yourself. He doesn't believe in tests so thats the only good part about his classes, but he does do quizzes on the readings or assignments. Easy A, but Painful.

summary_comment: Constantine is an excellent instructor known for his enthusiasm and energy in teaching. While his Greek accent can be challenging at times, it does not detract from his ability to engage students. He is highly recommended for his supportive nature and eagerness to help, making his classes a positive experience.

Ratings.comment: Constantine is a great instructor.  Very interested in teaching and sounds like he was a real athlete back in the day.  He is from Greece so his accent is tough a bit at times but that is not a deterant for taking the class.  All assignments are super easy.  I would definately recomend this course
Great instructor, with lots of energy.  Would recommend.
Mr. Psimopoulos is always very excited about teaching and he is very helpful. He is so eager to answering questions. His class cheered me up every day. One of the best experiences!

summary_comment: The professor is an excellent trainer who effectively pushes students to improve their skills while being mindful of their current abilities. Students find his approach refreshing compared to traditional university classes and highly recommend giving his training a try.

Ratings.comment: Great trainer! Pushes you to ride better, but is very attentive to your skill level. This was a great respite from regular university classes. Worth trying at least once!

summary_comment: This professor is highly regarded for his enthusiasm and deep knowledge in physical education, particularly in racquetball. Students appreciate his willingness to help clarify complex topics and his positive rapport with them. He emphasizes the importance of reading the assigned book and keeping notes, and is consistently praised for his teaching quality.

Ratings.comment: One of the most enthusiastic teachers I have ever had. Sometimes details can be difficult to grasp but he will work with you as much as you need for clarification. Has a great rapport with his students and is very knowledgeable on all thing PE. One of the best teachers I've ever had.

Jim's a good man. We have had him a few times and I have yet to ever hear any major complaints. Buy the book with this instructor and always keep a notebook with every handout. Every class we have had him for, hes been big on these things.

This guy was great at teaching how to play racquetball.  I already knew how to play coming into the class, but it was a fun class to take and he seemed like he knew what he was talking about even thought I never listened.  Fun class I recommend taking it with him, i have heard that other teachers are bad at this one.

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for his engaging and humorous teaching style, with students finding the classes both enjoyable and informative. Despite the vast amount of knowledge shared, some students note that the class covers a lot of material in a short time, leaving them feeling they did not gain practical skills such as officiating.

Ratings.comment: Great guy, has a lot of fun in the classroom.  Is very funny and very knowledgeable about the game of basketball. That being said, after taking the class, I don't feel like I would be capable of officiating a game very well. I don't think it is his fault, more of the class structure (lots of info, little time).
Funny, interesting, loved going to this class
Very knowledgeable. Funny guy

summary_comment: This professor excels in teaching with a deep understanding of golf and practical industry knowledge, making complex concepts accessible and relevant to students.

Ratings.comment: Terrific, understands golf and is in the profession!

summary_comment: Lauren is an excellent professor who makes her classes enjoyable and easy, particularly in activities-based courses like volleyball, where she focuses on practical engagement rather than rigorous drills. In EDUPAES 312, she is highly regarded for her knowledge and fairness, though her tests are challenging, making her a demanding yet effective lecturer.

Ratings.comment: I had Lauren for a Volleyball class. Easiest class I have ever taken. All you do is play the entire time. Don't do any drills or anything you don't want to do. She talks to you for 5 minutes during the class about technique then just lets you play. Automatic A if you go to class

Very knowledgeable, fair and a good lecturer.  Tests are a challenge, so take them seriously.  Doesn't slack from the chemistry.  Very good professor! Class was EDUPAES 312.  The boxes didn't allow for that format on Rate My Professor.

summary_comment: Professor Singh's teaching style is inconsistent and often confusing, with classes dragging due to off-topic discussions and difficulty finding relevant material for online quizzes. Despite some helpful guided notes, her lack of control over class time and fairness, along with unprofessional behavior like constant microphone use, significantly impact the learning experience.

Ratings.comment: This class started of interesting, but Professor Singh is all over the place. While the content is interesting, it drags. The online quizzes are sometimes over things we have never discussed in class, and really hard to find in the book. She emphasizes the importance of varied teaching styles, but doesn't implement them in her own class. Easy A

She shrieks into the microphone but then talks in a low voice when she's away and talking about a story. Gets off topic too much, but her guided notes are helpful. The time usually flies by. She doesn't have much control over the class though.

Gawdaweful! Can't start or finish on time.  Shrieks continuously into microphone.  Inconsistent, unfair, biased and bigoted.  Talks about importance of parent teacher communication, but all "stories" are of opelessly evil parents.

summary_comment: This professor is highly effective, significantly enhancing students' skills while making learning enjoyable. Students appreciate her clear and fair policies, grading, and testing methods. Her classes are widely regarded as among the best in the curriculum.

Ratings.comment: I learned so much in this class!! I started out barely being able to do a cartwheel and now I can do a back handspring. I had so much fun! I looked forward to class all the time and I wish I could take this again! Her policies, grading, and testing are very clear and fair.  Too bad all college classes aren't this great!!!

summary_comment: Carrie is an outstanding instructor who effectively tailors her yoga classes to meet the needs of each student, ensuring detailed guidance and adjustments. Her energetic presence and genuine care for her students' growth create a dynamic and enjoyable learning environment.

Ratings.comment: Carrie is an excellent instructor who genuinely cares about the growth of her students. She does a superb job of breaking down yoga poses and adjusting the difficulty according to each student's ability. She is always energetic and her good mood is often infectious.
She did a great job of determining each individual's level and pushing us to go further. It's a fast-paced class, but if you do what you're supposed to, it's fun and easy to get an A.
She is great. Never had done yoga before in my life. She went through every pose in detail before having the class do it. Very helpful if any pose is uncomfortable. Fun class.

summary_comment: No comments available

Professor Simonian is highly regarded for his engaging and humorous teaching style across various physical education classes, including boxing and fencing. Students consistently praise his ability to make complex subjects accessible and enjoyable, often encouraging others to enroll in his classes to experience his clear explanations and lively demeanor firsthand.

Ratings.comment: i loved this professor.  his boxing class was a lot of fun and i really learned about the sport.  he was very helpful and i really want to take another one of his classes!
I love this little guy.  I took boxing from him, and he's hilarious.  Definitely look for one of his classes for a phys ed requirement.
I had Professor Simonian for fencing 1 and loved the class. Pay attention, have some fun, learn a very interesting class. He explains everything clearly and is exceedingly funny too!

summary_comment: The professor has mixed reviews; while some students found him to be a fantastic, knowledgeable instructor with a passion for martial arts who strictly enforced attendance, others criticized his frequent class cancellations and strict attendance policies, noting that he left abruptly during one session, causing confusion. Overall, the class experience varied widely.

Ratings.comment: He canceled classes a lot! More than you expected! Also, very strict on attendance. He got mad at one student on one of classes, and then he just left. The rest of us were so confused. If you want to learn real thing for boxing, don't take his class. Not recommend.
Fantastic instructor, great class

Mark is a great instructor who is very educated in self defense and Martial Arts. He has several black belts and is an instructor for the military too. Class was awesome and I never wanted to miss it, and I never did. Judo was awesome and I'm excited for Karate in the fall.

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for her exceptional teaching quality, described as both engaging and kind. Students particularly praise her Rhythmic Aerobics class, expressing a strong desire to retake it.

Ratings.comment: Awesome instructor and so sweet!!! I loved her Rhythmic Aerobics class and I wish I could take it again!

summary_comment: Professor Demay is an effective and caring instructor who is known for his patience and willingness to help students succeed. While the material can be dry, Demay makes an effort to assist students in understanding the content, and many students appreciate his approachable nature and dedication to their academic progress.

Ratings.comment: Really nice guy and is funny. Class was partially online, took quiz'so online and watched major information videos on carmim. Have to go to class or you will fail.  Class was recitation where he went over a power point and answered questions.

Required freshman survey no one wanted to attend. Material is boring but that's not Demay's fault. Teacher (Demay) is easy, nice, and willing (and wanting) to help you succeed and progress in academic career. For sure a good teacher.
Dan is a great teacher.  He is very patient and cares that his students understand the material.  I would definitely take another class taught by him.

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for his friendly and approachable demeanor, genuinely wanting students to succeed. His classes provide insightful analysis of sports society, encouraging critical thinking. While some find his class very easy and even feel it may be a waste of time, others appreciate his flexibility and genuine interest in students' well-being.

Ratings.comment: He is friendly and approachable if you have questions. Really wants to see his students succeed. Didn't treat us like he was above us. You really learn things about the society of sports college/professionally that make you question things. Interesting class.

Nice guy and his class is very easy. He's a grad student so he understands how hard college is and he's very flexible about the work. Easiest class i've had but not in a good way. Felt like I was wasting my time attending. He thinks he's funny, and he's very friendly, likes to hear students stories and tells some of his own.

summary_comment: Lindsay is an effective and enthusiastic teacher who makes the subject of sports history engaging and enjoyable through interactive methods and group projects. While the course requires significant effort and reading, students find her teaching approachable and valuable, with helpful resources provided for exams.

Ratings.comment: EduPAES 211 - Lindsay actually  made learning about sports history fun and interesting. Group projects ended up being pretty fun. The class was a LOT of work and a lot of reading but I have to say that I learned a lot. She was a great teacher and very interested in what she was teaching.

An excellent teacher, she is very enthusiastic about the topic and does a good job of getting everyone involved in fun ways.  Quizzes can be challenging, but she provided a study guide for the midterm and the finals, which helped a lot.

She is a good teacher, but it is no different, nor is it easier, than any other history class.  I was under the impression that it was, but found it equal to my American history class.  Topic of sports is interesting though.

summary_comment: This professor is known for creating an engaging and humorous classroom atmosphere that keeps students entertained. However, students also report significant issues with the grading process, finding it overly rigorous and delayed. Overall, the class is more entertaining to observe than to participate in due to these challenges.

Ratings.comment: If you want to take a class where you can sit and continuosly laugh at the guy teaching it, this is the class to take.  If you want a class where the guy teaching it takes grading WAY too seriously, take this class.  It's sport for the spectator...what a joke.  If you are lucky he will post the notes up 6Hrs before class, and the grades 2wks after.

summary_comment: This professor is consistently praised for his high teaching quality, keeping classes engaging and interesting across multiple courses. Students find his classes easy while still intellectually stimulating.

Ratings.comment: Had him for 3 different classes. Best teacher and keeps class interesting.
Easy class and very interesting.
He is the best teacher ive ever had.

summary_comment: The professor is known for delivering an easily graded class with no exams, making it one of the more lenient two-credit-hour options available. Students find the course to be quite forgiving in terms of grading criteria.

Ratings.comment: Class was graded super easy.  No exams, so probably one of the easiest two credit hour classes

summary_comment: Professor Spencer offers a straightforward approach to earning high grades, emphasizing consistent attendance and effort. Students appreciate his kindness and willingness to assist, contributing to a positive learning environment.

Ratings.comment: Just show up and work out and you have an A.  Spencer is very nice and helpful.

summary_comment: The professor is highly regarded for her engaging and effective teaching methods in self-defense, imparting both practical skills and valuable life lessons. Students praise her encouraging atmosphere and her humorous teaching style, noting that she is an excellent role model, especially for empowering women to stand up for themselves.

Ratings.comment: Fun self defense instructor. She is great and teaches you not only how to defend yourself but a lot about life

Deb is an amazing self defense teacher.  She really helped me to stick up for myself and her class ended up being my favorite for the year.  Very encouraging atmosphere.  She talks a lot and yells, too but she is hilarious and I wish she taught real classes.

Awesome women's self defense teacher, she taught me so much. She has a kind of in your face attitude but it's a great because she is a role model for girls who need to stand up for themselves. I wish she taught more classes, I'd definitely take them.
